	 	•	Cancellation policies may be superseded by the Guest Refund Policy, safety cancellations, or extenuating circumstances. Please review these exceptions.<br>
	  
	 	•	If the guest books a long term stay and decides to cancel the long term agreement before the start date, the first payment is paid to the host in full.<br>
	 	•	If the guest books a long term stay and decides to cancel the long term agreement during their stay, the guest must use the online alteration tool in order to agree to a new checkout date. Regardless of the checkout date chosen, the guest is required to pay the host for the 30 days following the cancellation date, or up to the end date of the guest's original reservation if the remaining days of the original reservation is less than 30 days.<br>
		
		Extenuating Circumstances<br>
		Sometimes extenuating circumstances arise that affect travel plans. In extreme cases, Stayhappi may override the host's cancellation policy (flexible, moderate, strict) and make refund decisions. Such cases will be contingent on proper documentation, where valid, and include:<br>
			•	Death in the guest's family<br>
			•	Serious illness of the guest or a guest's family member<br>
			•	Natural disaster in the destination<br>
			•	Political unrest in the destination<br>
			•	Jury duty or other similar civil obligations<br>

		
